profile: 2012 and 2013 Consumer Choice Award winner for Chimney Services. A-1 Quality Chimney is an award-winning, full-service chimney company that has been serving homeowners in Toronto and surrounding areas for 30 years. Chimney cleaning, masonry repair and general maintenance is essential to preventing fire and ensuring safe operation of wood, oil, coal and gas burning appliances. With over 60,000 customers, we service thousands of fireplaces, wood stoves, pizza ovens, gas fireplaces, furnaces and other heating appliances. When it comes to chimney repairs and chimney rebuilds, we are able to address any masonry issues that arise. Above the roof line, chimneys bear the brunt of our cold winters and hot summers and diagnosing and addressing masonry issues is our specialty. Once you are ready for your repairs, we’ll get it done, on-time and on-budget. Having been in the business for so long, most of our customers come back to us year after year. And so we strive to give you the best service we can and ensure you and your family are safe and warm.

profile:
Metro Chimney specializes in chimney rebuilds, tuck pointing, and chimney sweeping and fireplace inspection services. 

With our service yard located in the Leaside area, Metro Chimney has serviced countless homes in Rosedale, Moore Park, Forest Hill and the Yonge and Eglinton areas. 

Chimney and fireplace inspection is a very important part of fireplace safety. When you call Metro Chimney, we don't just show up to sweep your chimney, we inspect it with a WETT-certified mason who builds and restores fireplaces. We provide fireplace restorations, firebox rebuilds, and more!


When your no-mess chimney cleaning is being performed, we are looking at your hearth and hearth extension, your firebox and damper, as well as your mantel, smoke chamber and what type of liner you have. We are inspecting your chimney, above and below the roofline, looking at the brick or stonework for any damage that may require our attention. Call or email us today to find out more!

profile:
Standing above the roofline, chimneys are fully exposed to rain and snow and are affected by winter's freeze/thaw cycles. They are therefore one of the first places on a house to deteriorate.  This deterioration usually takes many years to begin but then progresses rapidly.  Cracked or spalled bricks, damaged flue tiles or concrete caps, or a leaning structure are signs that the chimney needs immediate attention.
 
Top Hat Chimney specializes in all aspects of chimney repair and rebuilding.  Our brick masons are unsurpassed in their level of expertise, and take pride in their workmanship.   They take great care to protect the roof and ground so that all work will be completed in a clean and safe manner.
 
All of our work is guaranteed against defect in materials and workmanship.
 
We are happy to provide references from other satisfied customers in your area.
 
The burning of wood leaves highly flammable deposits in the chimney flue and smoke chamber.  Regular cleaning and inspection are essential in the prevention of chimney fires.
 
All of our expert technicians are WETT certified and employ the most up-to-date chimney cleaning techniques. Care is always taken to insure that there is no mess in the home.
 
A basic chimney sweep includes :
 
- cleaning of the chimney flue, smoke chamber, and smoke shelf
- damper adjustment
- basic  inspection.
 
Also Available :
 
- nest and blockage removal
- detailed WETT reports
- chimney caps and accesories
- special rates for multi-unit properties
